benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{accountEmailId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account email audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid GET request returns 200 with a JSON array of AuditLog objects (fields: id, changeType, changedBy, changeDate, history) (TC01, TC15, TC16)
Empty response when no audit logs exist (TC02)
Authorization scenarios: 401 for missing/invalid tokens (TC07, TC08)
Not found errors: 404 for missing account (TC03) and missing account email (TC04)
Bad request errors: 400 for invalid accountId format (TC05) and invalid accountEmailId format (TC06); security input tests (TC13, TC14)
Service errors: 503 when API service unavailable (TC09); 504 Gateway Timeout when downstream slow (TC12)
Large dataset handling: >1000 audit logs and performance target (TC11)
Data integrity: Correct ordering by changeDate descending (TC15) and backward compatibility of schema (TC16)
Special scenarios: accessibility in UI (TC17), empty/partially populated DB states (TC18, TC19)
gaps: Pagination: no explicit tests for paging through results (page size/page number)
Rate limiting: no tests for throttling or repeated requests
Caching headers: no tests for ETag/Cache-Control
Authorization nuance: test for forbidden (403) vs unauthorized (401) explicit permissions
Server-side error variety: no 500 Internal Server Error scenario
Edge cases: more invalid inputs or malformed URLs beyond those in TC13/TC14
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify pageSize, pageNumber, and total results
Add tests for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure throttling and quotas
Add caching headers tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and conditional requests
Add a 500 Internal Server Error scenario to exercise server-side failure handling
Consider consolidating UI accessibility tests with a dedicated UI test plan or story
